---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import HeroSection from '../components/HeroSection.astro';
import CTAButton from '../components/CTAButton.astro';
import FAQSection from '../components/FAQSection.astro';
import RelatedCare from '../components/RelatedCare.astro';
import { Check } from '@lucide/astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Specialized Laboratory Testing in Halifax"
  description="Private specialized laboratory testing in Halifax, including selected heavy metal, organic acid, infection, environmental exposure and genetic assessments."
  focusKeyword="functional medicine testing Halifax"
>
  <HeroSection
    title="Specialized Testing"
    compact
    image={{ src: "/images/lab-testing/specialized-testing.webp", alt: "Blood draw preparation for specialized testing", aspect: "video" }}
  >
    <p>Specialized laboratory testing can extend an assessment beyond routine blood work. Available options include selected exposure, metabolic, infection and genetic tests, with <strong class="text-white">no specialist referral required</strong>.</p>
  </HeroSection>

  <!-- The Problem with Standard Testing -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-emerald-50">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950 mb-6">A Broader Range of Testing Options</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">
          <p>
            Some patients want to investigate concerns that are not included in routine blood work, or have persistent symptoms despite previous medical assessment. Private testing offers access to additional laboratory options and more time to review what each test measures.
          </p>
          <p>
            Routine medical testing remains important and should not be replaced when primary care, imaging or specialist assessment is needed. Specialized panels can be considered alongside that care, with their costs, evidence and limitations explained before ordering.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-lg card-hover">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-emerald-950 mb-6">What Specialized Testing May Assess</h3>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <Check class="w-6 h-6 text-emerald-600 mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" />
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-emerald-950">Selected exposures</span>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Specific metals or environmental chemicals when there is a relevant exposure history</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <Check class="w-6 h-6 text-emerald-600 mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" />
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-emerald-950">Urinary metabolites</span>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Organic acid measurements that provide a descriptive metabolic profile</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <Check class="w-6 h-6 text-emerald-600 mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" />
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-emerald-950">Selected infections</span>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Targeted antibody, antigen or molecular testing based on symptoms and exposure history</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <Check class="w-6 h-6 text-emerald-600 mt-1 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" />
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-emerald-950">Selected genetic variants</span>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Variants such as MTHFR, interpreted with health history and related blood markers</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Specialized Testing Panel Cards -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-white">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950 mb-4">Specialized Testing Options</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Dr. MacLeod reviews your previous results, health history and testing priorities, recommends suitable options and discusses any additional panels you want to consider.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <!-- Heavy Metal Assessment -->
        <div class="bg-emerald-50 rounded-2xl p-6 card-hover">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-emerald-700 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <span class="text-white font-bold text-sm">Hg/Pb</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-emerald-950 mb-2">Heavy Metal Assessment</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">Measures selected elements such as mercury, lead, arsenic or cadmium. The specimen and interpretation depend on the element, the suspected source and the timing of exposure.</p>
          <div class="text-xs text-slate-600">
            <span class="font-medium">Methods:</span> Blood or urine, depending on the assessment<br>
            <span class="font-medium text-emerald-700">Consider when:</span> There is a relevant environmental or occupational exposure
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Organic Acids -->
        <div class="bg-emerald-50 rounded-2xl p-6 card-hover">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-emerald-700 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <span class="text-white font-bold text-sm">OAT</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-emerald-950 mb-2">Organic Acids Test (OAT)</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">Measures a range of metabolites in urine. The pattern may provide supplementary information about metabolic pathways, but it does not diagnose a specific cause of fatigue or other symptoms on its own.</p>
          <div class="text-xs text-slate-600">
            <span class="font-medium">Method:</span> First morning urine sample<br>
            <span class="font-medium text-emerald-700">Consider when:</span> A broader metabolic profile is requested after initial assessment
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Chronic Infection Panels -->
        <div class="bg-emerald-50 rounded-2xl p-6 card-hover">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-emerald-700 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <span class="text-white font-bold text-sm">Inf</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-emerald-950 mb-2">Chronic Infection Panels</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">Targeted testing may include Epstein-Barr virus, Lyme disease or other infections. The type of test and timing are selected according to symptoms, exposure history and previous results.</p>
          <div class="text-xs text-slate-600">
            <span class="font-medium">May include:</span> Antibody, antigen or molecular testing<br>
            <span class="font-medium text-emerald-700">Important:</span> Positive and negative results require clinical interpretation
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Environmental Toxins -->
        <div class="bg-emerald-50 rounded-2xl p-6 card-hover">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-emerald-700 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <span class="text-white font-bold text-sm">Tox</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-emerald-950 mb-2">Environmental Toxins</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">Some private laboratories measure metabolites associated with selected pesticides, plasticizers or solvents. Availability and the clinical usefulness of individual markers vary.</p>
          <div class="text-xs text-slate-600">
            <span class="font-medium">Method:</span> Urine testing<br>
            <span class="font-medium text-emerald-700">Consider when:</span> There is a specific exposure concern to investigate
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Methylation Panel -->
        <div class="bg-emerald-50 rounded-2xl p-6 card-hover">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-emerald-700 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <span class="text-white font-bold text-sm">MTHF</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-emerald-950 mb-2">Methylation Panel</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">May combine selected genetic variants with blood markers such as homocysteine, folate and vitamin B12. A genetic variant does not by itself diagnose impaired metabolism or determine treatment.</p>
          <div class="text-xs text-slate-600">
            <span class="font-medium">Markers:</span> Homocysteine, MTHFR, COMT, folate, B12<br>
            <span class="font-medium text-emerald-700">Interpretation:</span> Results are reviewed with related blood work and health history
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Broader assessment -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-emerald-950">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-serif font-medium text-white mb-6">A Broader Assessment for Complex Histories</h2>
          <div class="prose prose-lg prose-invert">
            <p class="text-white/90">
              Persistent or multi-system symptoms often require information from several sources: medical history, physical examination, routine laboratory work, imaging or specialist assessment, and sometimes additional private testing.
            </p>
            <p class="text-white/90">
              Specialized tests can add another layer when you want to investigate a particular exposure, infection, metabolic profile or genetic variant. Their findings are reviewed alongside established tests rather than treated as a complete explanation on their own.
            </p>
            <p class="text-white/90">
              Dr. MacLeod will explain which options fit your priorities, what the results can and cannot establish, and the cost before you decide how broad you want the assessment to be.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white/10 backdrop-blur rounded-2xl p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-6">When to Consider Specialized Testing</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-4">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-white/90">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-emerald-400 mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Routine blood work has not explained persistent symptoms</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-white/90">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-emerald-400 mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Chronic fatigue that doesn't improve with rest or lifestyle changes</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-white/90">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-emerald-400 mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Multiple symptoms across different body systems</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-white/90">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-emerald-400 mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>History of environmental or occupational exposure</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-white/90">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-emerald-400 mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Post-viral symptoms that haven't resolved (long COVID, post-EBV)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-white/90">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-emerald-400 mt-1 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Family history of autoimmune, neurological or metabolic conditions</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Information to review -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-emerald-50">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950 mb-4">Concerns to Review During Your Consultation</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-lg card-hover">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-emerald-950 mb-4">Neurological & Cognitive</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            {['Persistent brain fog or poor memory', 'Numbness, tingling or neuropathy', 'Mood swings, anxiety or depression', 'Difficulty concentrating', 'Headaches or migraines'].map(symptom => (
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2 text-slate-700">
                <Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-600 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" />
                {symptom}
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-lg card-hover">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-emerald-950 mb-4">Systemic & Physical</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            {['Chronic fatigue unresponsive to treatment', 'Joint and muscle pain without clear cause', 'Chemical sensitivities or medication reactions', 'Hormonal issues despite standard treatment', 'Recurrent infections or immune dysfunction', 'Symptoms that started after an illness or exposure'].map(symptom => (
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2 text-slate-700">
                <Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-600 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true" />
                {symptom}
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Nova Scotia Context -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-white">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-serif font-medium text-emerald-950 mb-6">Accessing Specialized Testing in Nova Scotia</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-lg text-slate-600">
          <p>
            Publicly funded testing and private laboratory testing serve different roles. Primary care and specialist pathways provide essential diagnostic assessment, while private laboratories can offer additional tests that are not routinely funded or are difficult to access through the public system.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>No family doctor or specialist referral is required to discuss private testing through the practice</li>
            <li>Available options, expected costs and collection instructions are reviewed before ordering</li>
            <li>Additional tests you want to explore can be discussed as part of the testing plan</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Specialized testing complements rather than replaces conventional care. Results that require medical diagnosis, imaging, urgent assessment or specialist treatment are directed to the appropriate healthcare service, and copies can be shared with your existing providers.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <RelatedCare
    title="Related Testing"
    hubHref="/lab-testing/"
    hubLabel="Lab Testing"
    links={[
      { title: 'Digestive Health Testing', href: '/digestive-health-testing/' },
      { title: 'Hormone Testing', href: '/hormone-testing/' },
      { title: 'Wellness Blood Work', href: '/wellness-blood-work/' },
    ]}
  />

  <FAQSection bg="white" items={[
          { question: "Can I request a specific specialized test?", answer: "<p>Yes. Bring the name of the test or the area you want investigated to your consultation. I will explain the available options, recommend a suitable testing plan and review the cost and limitations with you before anything is ordered.</p>" },
          { question: "How much do specialized tests cost?", answer: "<p>Costs vary by laboratory and panel. The complete price is reviewed before ordering so you can decide whether to proceed with a focused test or a broader assessment. Some extended health plans may provide partial laboratory coverage.</p>" },
          { question: "How reliable are specialized tests?", answer: "<p>Reliability and clinical usefulness vary by test. Laboratory accuracy does not always mean that every reported marker has a well-established role in diagnosis or treatment. I will explain the evidence and limitations that apply to the testing you are considering.</p>" },
          { question: "Should I start with routine blood work or specialized testing?", answer: "<p>Routine blood work often provides important baseline information and may be completed before or alongside specialized testing. The order depends on your previous results, symptoms, exposure history and the testing you want to pursue.</p>" },
          { question: "Can you work with my existing healthcare team?", answer: "<p>Yes. Specialized testing can complement care from your family doctor, specialist or other healthcare providers. You can receive copies of your results, and findings that require medical investigation or treatment can be shared with the appropriate provider.</p>" },
        ]} />

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-emerald-950">
    <div class="section-shell">
      <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-serif font-medium text-white mb-6">Plan Your Specialized Testing</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-white/90 mb-8">
          Book an initial consultation to review your concerns, previous results and the specialized tests you would like to explore.
        </p>
        <CTAButton source="specialized-testing-cta" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
